 of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Agnes Ferrers was born in 1105, in Greenham, Berkshire, England, United Kingdom, her father, Robert de Ferrières 1st Earl of Derby, was 43 and her mother, Hawise de Vitré, was 36. She had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Ralph de Paganell. She died in 1130, in Warwickshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 25."},"et":{"1105–1130":"1105–1130","1086–1150":"1086–1150","1092–Male":"1092–Surnud","1100–1162":"1100–1162","1105–1151":"1105–1151","1107–Female":"1107–Surnud","1118–Female":"1118–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1095–1153":"1095–1153","1125–1194":"1125–1194","1144–1209":"1144–1209","1062–1139":"1062–1139","1069–1139":"1069–1139","1153":"1153","1130":"1130","1086":"1086","1151":"1151","1162":"1162","1062":"1062","1194":"1194","1095":"1095","1150":"1150","1092":"1092","1118":"1118","1107":"1107","1139":"1139","1105":"1105","1125":"1125","1069":"1069","1144":"1144","1100":"1100","about 1125":"umbes 1125","1209":"1209","Dudley, Warwickshire, England":"Warwickshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Greenham, Newbury, Berkshire, England":"Greenham, Berkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Les Moutiers-Hubert, Calvados, Basse-Normandie, France":"Les Moutiers-Hubert, Calvados, Basse-Normandie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1105–1130":"1105–1130","1086–1150":"1086–1150","1092–Male":"1092–Kuollut","1100–1162":"1100–1162","1105–1151":"1105–1151","1107–Female":"1107–Kuollut","1118–Female":"1118–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1095–1153":"1095–1153","1125–1194":"1125–1194","1144–1209":"1144–1209","1062–1139":"1062–1139","1069–1139":"1069–1139","1153":"1153","1130":"1130","1086":"1086","1151":"1151","1162":"1162","1062":"1062","1194":"1194",